==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|lang=la|correctus||improved, amended, correct}}, past participle of {{term|lang=la|corrigere}}, {{term|lang=la|conrigere||to make straight, make right, make better, improve, correct}}, from {{term|lang=la|com-||together}} + {{term|lang=la|regere||to make straight, rule}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/kəˈɹɛkt/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/k@"rEkt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-correct.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛkt}}
* {{hyphenation|cor|rect}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Free from [[error]]; true; the state of having an affirmed [[truth]].
# With good [[manners]]; [[well behaved]]; conforming with accepted standards of behaviour.

